column1: LLM Engineer â€“ AI-Assisted RTL Integration,"ROLE : LLM Engineer â€“ AI-Assisted RTL Integration

LLM Engineer with expertise in prompt engineering, dataset creation, fine-tuning, and deployment of on-premises open-source LLMs for RTL (Register Transfer Level) design. The ideal candidate will work closely with RTL domain experts to develop and optimize AI-assisted RTL integration workflows.
The role involves prompt engineering, output validation and re-prompting, fine-tuning of LLMs when necessary, and building datasets to enhance model accuracy using the latest AI/ML technologies.
Deploy and optimize open-source LLMs on-premises for RTL integration.
Develop custom pipelines for LLM-assisted RTL design, analysis, and verification.
Work with RTL experts to fine-tune prompts for best performance.
Design, refine, and test effective prompts for RTL integration tasks.
Continuously evaluate LLM responses and develop strategies for output validation.
Implement re-prompting techniques to improve accuracy and efficiency.
Identify gaps in model accuracy and develop datasets for model retraining.
Collect, clean, and curate RTL-specific datasets to improve model performance.
Fine-tune LLMs using state-of-the-art training frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face).
Experiment with latest AI/ML techniques to optimize LLM efficiency for RTL workflows.
Implement evaluation metrics to measure model performance in RTL tasks.
Conduct benchmarking and performance tuning to ensure model accuracy.

LLM Engineer with expertise in prompt engineering, dataset creation, fine-tuning, and deployment of on-premises open-source LLMs for RTL (Register Transfer Level) design. The ideal candidate will work closely with RTL domain experts to develop and optimize AI-assisted RTL integration workflows.
The role involves prompt engineering, output validation and re-prompting, fine-tuning of LLMs when necessary, and building datasets to enhance model accuracy using the latest AI/ML technologies.

column2: • Deploy and optimize open-source LLMs on-premises for RTL integration.
• Develop custom pipelines for LLM-assisted RTL design, analysis, and verification.
• Work with RTL experts to fine-tune prompts for best performance.
• Design, refine, and test effective prompts for RTL integration tasks.
• Continuously evaluate LLM responses and develop strategies for output validation.
• Implement re-prompting techniques to improve accuracy and efficiency.
• Identify gaps in model accuracy and develop datasets for model retraining.
• Collect, clean, and curate RTL-specific datasets to improve model performance.
• Fine-tune LLMs using state-of-the-art training frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face).
• Experiment with latest AI/ML techniques to optimize LLM efficiency for RTL workflows.
• Implement evaluation metrics to measure model performance in RTL tasks.
• Conduct benchmarking and performance tuning to ensure model accuracy.
• Develop feedback loops for continuous improvement of LLM-assisted RTL processes.
• Work closely with RTL engineers to understand domain challenges.
• Stay up to date with the latest advancements in AI/ML and hardware design automation.
• Evaluate and implement state-of-the-art LLM architectures for RTL-specific applications.
• Strong expertise in LLMs – Open-source models like Llama, Falcon, Mistral, or GPT-based architectures.
• Experience in fine-tuning LLMs using PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Hugging Face.
• Prompt engineering expertise – Ability to craft optimized prompts for RTL tasks.
• Understanding of RTL design (basic knowledge preferred) and how AI can assist in hardware workflows.
• Experience in data collection, preprocessing, and synthetic dataset creation for fine-tuning.
• Familiarity with LLM inference optimization techniques (e.g., quantization, pruning).
• Strong coding skills in Python and frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex, or OpenAI APIs.
• Experience with containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and on-prem model hosting.

column9: Job Description :TitleÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  : Senior Software DeveloperTypeÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  : 100% RemoteLocationÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  : RemoteDurationÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  : 6 monthsMOIÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  : VirtualDeep knowledge of the Palantir Foundry platform is required - Oil and Gas is a Plus.A ""Palantir Foundry full stack developer"" is a software engineer who specializes in building applications on the Palantir Foundry platform, utilizing both front-end and back-end development skills to create comprehensive data-driven applications within the Foundry environment, including user interfaces, data pipelines, and complex data analysis features.Key points about a Palantir Foundry full stack developer :Platform expertise : They have deep knowledge of the Palantir Foundry platform, including its tools like Workshop, Quiver, and Slate, which are used to design data workflows, build visualizations, and create user interfaces.Full-stack development : They are proficient in both front-end technologies (like JavaScript, HTML, CSS) to create user-friendly interfaces and back-end technologies (like Python, Java) to manage data processing and application logic.Data integration skills : They can design and implement data pipelines to integrate data from various sources into the Foundry platform, ensuring data quality and consistency.Collaboration with stakeholders : They work closely with subject matter experts (SMEs) to understand business requirements and translate them into functional applications within Foundry.Application development focus : Their primary responsibility is to develop custom applications on the Foundry platform, which can include complex data analysis tools, decision support systems, and operational dashboards.Â

I was trying to reach you regarding for Job opportunity.

LLM Engineer with expertise in prompt engineering, dataset creation, fine-tuning, and deployment of on-premises open-source LLMs for RTL (Register Transfer Level) design. The ideal candidate will work closely with RTL domain experts to develop and optimize AI-assisted RTL integration workflows.
The role involves prompt engineering, output validation and re-prompting, fine-tuning of LLMs when necessary, and building datasets to enhance model accuracy using the latest AI/ML technologies.

column2: • Deploy and optimize open-source LLMs on-premises for RTL integration.
• Develop custom pipelines for LLM-assisted RTL design, analysis, and verification.
• Work with RTL experts to fine-tune prompts for best performance.
• Design, refine, and test effective prompts for RTL integration tasks.
• Continuously evaluate LLM responses and develop strategies for output validation.
• Implement re-prompting techniques to improve accuracy and efficiency.
• Identify gaps in model accuracy and develop datasets for model retraining.
• Collect, clean, and curate RTL-specific datasets to improve model performance.
• Fine-tune LLMs using state-of-the-art training frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face).
• Experiment with latest AI/ML techniques to optimize LLM efficiency for RTL workflows.
• Implement evaluation metrics to measure model performance in RTL tasks.
• Conduct benchmarking and performance tuning to ensure model accuracy.
• Develop feedback loops for continuous improvement of LLM-assisted RTL processes.
• Work closely with RTL engineers to understand domain challenges.
• Stay up to date with the latest advancements in AI/ML and hardware design automation.
• Evaluate and implement state-of-the-art LLM architectures for RTL-specific applications.
• Strong expertise in LLMs – Open-source models like Llama, Falcon, Mistral, or GPT-based architectures.
• Experience in fine-tuning LLMs using PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Hugging Face.
• Prompt engineering expertise – Ability to craft optimized prompts for RTL tasks.
• Understanding of RTL design (basic knowledge preferred) and how AI can assist in hardware workflows.
• Experience in data collection, preprocessing, and synthetic dataset creation for fine-tuning.
• Familiarity with LLM inference optimization techniques (e.g., quantization, pruning).
• Strong coding skills in Python and frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex, or OpenAI APIs.
• Experience with containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and on-prem model hosting.

Hope you’re doing good.
We do have a Longterm Remote opportunity for Sr. Data Engineer (Strong Snowflake)
Please share your updated resume and expected hourly rate if you are interested in this position.
Sr. Data Engineer (Strong Snowflake)
Duration: 3-6 months
Location: Remote
Sr. Data Engineer with deep Snowflake experience.

Our tech stack currently is Snowflake, AirByte, DBT, AirFlow, PlanetScale (Vitess MySQL). Now, this is not a standard request. What I mean by that is we need not just a Sr. Data Engineer. We need an absolute boss who bends metal with his mind, walks on water guru of Snowflake Data Engineer who could impress the creators of Snowflake. Not someone who simply ""has experience"" or even ""a lot of experience"".

column2: • Seeking a highly skilled Senior Data Engineer with deep expertise in Snowflake and a proven ability to design and optimize complex data architectures.
• Must possess mastery of modern data engineering tools, including AirByte, DBT, AirFlow, and PlanetScale (Vitess MySQL), with the ability to push these technologies to their limits.
• Beyond extensive experience, this role demands a true innovator—someone who can architect, optimize, and scale Snowflake environments at an elite level.
• Requires a strategic thinker who can lead data initiatives, solve intricate challenges, and drive performance improvements that set new industry standards.
• Ideal candidate is a visionary problem solver, capable of transforming complex data ecosystems with precision, efficiency, and technical excellence.

LLM Engineer with expertise in prompt engineering, dataset creation, fine-tuning, and deployment of on-premises open-source LLMs for RTL (Register Transfer Level) design. The ideal candidate will work closely with RTL domain experts to develop and optimize AI-assisted RTL integration workflows.
The role involves prompt engineering, output validation and re-prompting, fine-tuning of LLMs when necessary, and building datasets to enhance model accuracy using the latest AI/ML technologies.

column2: • Deploy and optimize open-source LLMs on-premises for RTL integration.
• Develop custom pipelines for LLM-assisted RTL design, analysis, and verification.
• Work with RTL experts to fine-tune prompts for best performance.
• Design, refine, and test effective prompts for RTL integration tasks.
• Continuously evaluate LLM responses and develop strategies for output validation.
• Implement re-prompting techniques to improve accuracy and efficiency.
• Identify gaps in model accuracy and develop datasets for model retraining.
• Collect, clean, and curate RTL-specific datasets to improve model performance.
• Fine-tune LLMs using state-of-the-art training frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face).
• Experiment with latest AI/ML techniques to optimize LLM efficiency for RTL workflows.
• Implement evaluation metrics to measure model performance in RTL tasks.
• Conduct benchmarking and performance tuning to ensure model accuracy.
• Develop feedback loops for continuous improvement of LLM-assisted RTL processes.
• Work closely with RTL engineers to understand domain challenges.
• Stay up to date with the latest advancements in AI/ML and hardware design automation.
• Evaluate and implement state-of-the-art LLM architectures for RTL-specific applications.
• Strong expertise in LLMs – Open-source models like Llama, Falcon, Mistral, or GPT-based architectures.
• Experience in fine-tuning LLMs using PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Hugging Face.
• Prompt engineering expertise – Ability to craft optimized prompts for RTL tasks.
• Understanding of RTL design (basic knowledge preferred) and how AI can assist in hardware workflows.
• Experience in data collection, preprocessing, and synthetic dataset creation for fine-tuning.
• Familiarity with LLM inference optimization techniques (e.g., quantization, pruning).
• Strong coding skills in Python and frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex, or OpenAI APIs.
• Experience with containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and on-prem model hosting.

column9: Role: Workday Testing LeadLocation: Chicago, ILMode of Work: HybridJob Description:Workday Testing Lead We are seeking an experienced Workday Testing Lead to oversee and manage the testing lifecycle for Workday implementations and enhancements.Â The ideal candidate will have a strong background in Workday HCM, Payroll, Financials, or other modules, with proven expertise in planning, executing, and delivering high-quality testing outcomes.Â Â Key Responsibilities:Â Lead the end-to-end testing process for Workday implementations, upgrades, or integrations, including planning, execution, and reporting.Â Collaborate with functional and technical teams to develop comprehensive test strategies and plans.Â Design and execute test cases for Workday modules such as HCM, Payroll, Financials, Time Tracking, and others.Â Manage and coordinate User Acceptance Testing (UAT), Regression Testing, and System Integration Testing (SIT).Â Identify, document, and track defects, ensuring timely resolution and retesting.Â Utilize testing tools and frameworks to optimize testing efficiency and accuracy.Â Provide guidance and mentorship to testing teams, ensuring adherence to best practices and standards.Â Communicate testing progress, risks, and issues to stakeholders and leadership.Â Ensure compliance with organizational policies, security standards, and regulatory requirements.Thanks & Regards,Anubhav JainÂ IT RecruiterHMG America LLCanubhav@hmgamerica.comhttp://www.hmgamerica.com

• Experience in fine-tuning LLMs using PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Hugging Face.
• Prompt engineering expertise – Ability to craft optimized prompts for RTL tasks.
• Understanding of RTL design (basic knowledge preferred) and how AI can assist in hardware workflows.
• Experience in data collection, preprocessing, and synthetic dataset creation for fine-tuning.
• Familiarity with LLM inference optimization techniques (e.g., quantization, pruning).
• Strong coding skills in Python and frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex, or OpenAI APIs.
• Experience with containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and on-prem model hosting.

column1: Data Engineer with Databricks - Hybrid - Lansing, MI, United States,"Job summary Title Data Engineer with Databricks - Hybrid Location Lansing, MI, United States Length and Terms: Long term - W2 or C2C Job description *** Very long term project initial PO for 1 year and usually the project goes for 3-5 years with this customer ***  ***Hybrid*** 2 days a week onsite*** ***In-person interview***  Description: The position is responsible for providing ongoing maintenance and support of the Michigan Disease Surveillance System (MDSS). MDSS is a complex application that supports communicable disease surveillance, registries, and case management systems that are critical to supporting effective responses to public health emergencies and reducing the burden of communicable diseases. MDSS is going through modernization to enhance stability and functionality of the system. With phase 1 already completed. The resource is integral to developing and maintaining and enhancing MDHHSâ€™ MDSS phase 1. Making sure automated processes are funtioning, streamlining critical business processes, data integrity, SEM/SUITE compliance, and securing the application.  The resource also performs as a technical lead and provides technical guidance to the other developers in the department.  As a technical lead, the resource participates in a variety of analytical assignments that provide for the enhancement, integration, maintenance, and implementation of projects.  The resource will also provides technical oversight to other developers in the team that support other critical applications . Not having a resource on staff will lead to MDHSS failing to maintain, enhance, and support the modernized MDSS that can lead to errors causing application outages, data integrity issues and can eventually lead to incorrect information being processed and reporting of the patient information. Required Skills 12+ years developing complex database systems. 8+ years Databricks. 8+ years using Elastic search, Kibanna. 8+ years using Python/Scala. 8+ years Oracle. 5+ years experience with Extract, Transform, and Load (ETL) processes and developing Data Pipelines. 5+ years experience with AWS. Over 5+ years experience with data warehousing, data visualization Tools, data integrity . Over 5+ years using CMM/CMMI Level 3 methods and practices. Over 5+ years implemented agile development processes including test driven development. Key Responsibilities:

column2: • Lead Genesys Development: Take ownership of designing, developing, and maintaining Genesys solutions (Genesys Cloud, Genesys Engage, or Genesys on-premises) for enterprise contact centers.

• Customization and Integration: Create advanced customizations using Genesys scripting languages (e.g., GVP, GML, CCXML) and integrate Genesys with various third-party applications (CRM, WFM, Databases, etc.).
• Mentor and Support Junior Developers: Provide technical leadership, guidance, and mentorship to junior developers and cross-functional teams on Genesys development and best practices.
• Troubleshooting and Issue Resolution: Resolve complex technical issues, identify system bottlenecks, and implement performance improvements to ensure smooth operations.
• System Architecture and Design: Collaborate with architects and other senior developers to design scalable, efficient, and reliable contact center systems and integrations.
• API Integration and Development: Develop and maintain custom APIs for integrating Genesys platforms with internal and third-party systems, including CRM, databases, and analytics tools.
• Monitoring and Performance Tuning: Ensure the Genesys environment operates at optimal performance, including analyzing system logs, optimizing configuration settings, and troubleshooting errors.

• Collaboration with Stakeholders: Work closely with business analysts, project managers, and other departments to gather requirements, design solutions, and deliver high-quality products that meet business needs.
• Documentation: Create and maintain detailed technical documentation for all custom development, system architecture, integrations, and best practices.
• Stay Updated on Genesys Features: Keep current with the latest updates in Genesys platforms, and evaluate how new features and tools can improve systems and processes.

Job Summary: We are seeking a highly skilled NetApp Certified Resource with 6 to 8 years of experience in NetApp Storage Grid and NetApp Storage Administration. The ideal candidate will work in a hybrid model during the day shift. This role does not require travel. The candidate will be responsible for managing and analyzing geospatial data to support our company's objectives and contribute to impactful projects that benefit society.
• Manage and analyze geospatial data to support various projects and initiatives.
• Oversee the administration and maintenance of NetApp Storage Grid systems.
• Provide technical expertise in NetApp Storage Administration to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
• Develop and implement data management strategies to enhance data accessibility and usability.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate geospatial data into business processes.
• Ensure data integrity and security by implementing best practices and protocols.
• Create detailed reports and visualizations to communicate findings and insights to stakeholders.
• Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to geospatial data and storage systems.
• Stay updated with the latest advancements in geospatial technologies and storage solutions.
• Train and mentor junior team members on geospatial data management and storage administration.
• Contribute to the development of policies and procedures for data management and storage.
• Support the company's objectives by providing accurate and timely geospatial data analysis.
• Enhance the company's impact on society by leveraging geospatial data to inform decision-making.
• Possess 6 to 8 years of experience in geospatial data analysis and NetApp Storage Grid.
• Demonstrate expertise in NetApp Storage Administration with a proven track record.
• Exhibit strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
• Show proficiency in data management and visualization tools.
• Have excellent communication and collaboration abilities.
• Display a commitment to staying current with industry trends and technologies.
Years of Experience:     8.00 Years of Experience

Job Summary: We are seeking a highly skilled NetApp Certified Resource with 6 to 8 years of experience in NetApp Storage Grid and NetApp Storage Administration. The ideal candidate will work in a hybrid model during the day shift. This role does not require travel. The candidate will be responsible for managing and analyzing geospatial data to support our company's objectives and contribute to impactful projects that benefit society.
• Manage and analyze geospatial data to support various projects and initiatives.
• Oversee the administration and maintenance of NetApp Storage Grid systems.
• Provide technical expertise in NetApp Storage Administration to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
• Develop and implement data management strategies to enhance data accessibility and usability.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate geospatial data into business processes.
• Ensure data integrity and security by implementing best practices and protocols.
• Create detailed reports and visualizations to communicate findings and insights to stakeholders.
• Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to geospatial data and storage systems.
• Stay updated with the latest advancements in geospatial technologies and storage solutions.
• Train and mentor junior team members on geospatial data management and storage administration.
• Contribute to the development of policies and procedures for data management and storage.
• Support the company's objectives by providing accurate and timely geospatial data analysis.
• Enhance the company's impact on society by leveraging geospatial data to inform decision-making.
• Possess 6 to 8 years of experience in geospatial data analysis and NetApp Storage Grid.
• Demonstrate expertise in NetApp Storage Administration with a proven track record.
• Exhibit strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
• Show proficiency in data management and visualization tools.
• Have excellent communication and collaboration abilities.
• Display a commitment to staying current with industry trends and technologies.
Years of Experience:     8.00 Years of Experience

Dear Professional,
Hope you are doing great today...

This is BABU, BDM FROM PANTAR SOLUTIONS INC, we are an Information Technology and Business Consulting firm specializing in Project-based Solutions and Professional Staffing Services. Please have a look at below position which is with our Client and let me know your interest ASAP. I would really appreciate if you could send me your MOST RECENT UPDATED RESUME:
Senior SAP Business Object Data Services (BODS) Developer with S/4 HANA Finance
Location: Charlotte, NC (3 days/ week hybrid. Tues-Thurs onsite)
Duration: 6-month contract w/ potential to extend
Kindly don’t share Fake/Mismatched/Junk Profiles

Need strong Senior SAP HANA BODS Developer with Data migration and data integration journey with S/4 HANA Finance, SQL, ETL, Blueprint / Design workshops, SAP Data Migration, SAP S4/ECC/ABAP,  creating and executing load programs to load data into SAP from Data Services/SAP using IDoc, BAPI, LTMC, LTMOM, LSMW & custom ABAP program load methods,  Data Quality module of Data Services including cleansing, matching & de-duplication of data, SAP Data Quality Management, SAP Simple Mail Transfer Protocol Exp.
Consultant LinkedIn profile must have been created before 2018
Need 8 - 10+yrs of IT Exp. Profiles || Need Passport number, I94, Travel History documents during submission for H4EAD/E3/TN1/H1/GC EAD/GC
JOB DESCRIPTION

Our global Fortune 500 client, with U.S. headquarters in Charlotte, NC, is a world class food service provider with a strong presence across the nation. Celebrating almost 30 years in North America, this employee-focused company has received honors for diversity and inclusion, innovation, health and wellness, and company culture. CRG has successfully placed over 220 employees within the last 7 years within this organization, known for its continuous growth opportunities, fantastic benefits package, innovative technology, flexible work environment, and collaborative culture.

This company is looking to contract a Senior SAP Business Object Data Services (BODS) Developer who will be charged with implementing SAP BODS and guide our Data migration and data integration journey with S/4 HANA Finance Transformation. You will be working as part of the SAP Technical team that is responsible for the development and support of all SAP applications across the company. This position will develop your knowledge in many aspects related to SAP operations and integrated IT systems.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Primary responsibilities of this role include the following:
Conduct Blueprint / Design workshops for the Data Conversion/Migration projects.
Identifies key drivers of a defined problem and proposes solutions.
Selects the most relevant ETL tools/techniques to meet specific business requirements.
Engages and works with implementation partner and comapny business partners, coordinates activities between work streams and identifies changes in scope.
Develops solutions to business problems through application of personal experience and methods and tools; validates solutions to subject matter experts.
Demonstrates accountability and contributions to the successful realization of business goals.
QUALIFICATIONS
5+ years of SAP Data Migration technical experience utilizing SAP Data Services (BODS) with strong SQL skills, SAP Information Steward and working knowledge of SAP S4/ECC/ABAP.

Worked on at least 2-3 Full Life Cycle Implementations in SAP including conducting Blueprint / Design workshops, requirements gathering, gap analysis, custom object development, data loading, unit testing, integration testing and go-live strategies.
Experience in review and approval process of the business rules/mapping document and convert functional specifications to technical specifications.
Designing ETL jobs to extract, cleanse, validate and transform data from SAP and non-SAP data sources.
Experience in creating and executing load programs to load data into SAP from Data Services/SAP using IDoc, BAPI, LTMC, LTMOM, LSMW & custom ABAP program load methods
Experience in Data Quality module of Data Services including cleansing, matching & de-duplication of data.
Developing data quality routines with real-time trigger-based alerts for data analysis utilizing SAP BODS Real Time jobs, SAP Data Quality Management and SAP Simple Mail Transfer Protocol

Defining systems strategy, developing systems requirements, designing and prototyping, testing, training, defining support procedures, and implementing practical business solutions under multiple deadlines.
Bachelor's degree or equivalent professional experience.
NICE TO HAVE
Experience creating and documenting functional and technical specifications.
Adept at implementing technology-enabled business solutions for clients as part of a high-talent team.
Strong written, presentation, communication, and relationship-management skills.
Strong problem solving and troubleshooting skills.
Adept at implementing technology-enabled business solutions for clients as part of a high-talent team.
Strong written, presentation, communication, and relationship-management skills.
Strong problem solving and troubleshooting skills.
Ability to peer review documentation.
Babu
Pantar Solutions Inc
1908 Cox Rd, Weddington, NC  28104
Email: babu (dot) s (at) pantarsolutions (dot) com

column9: Title: Epic Application AnalystLocation: Columbus, OhioMOI: SKypeDuration: 6 MOnthsÂ once in a weekInterviews will be done online via a Teams meeting.â€¢ 12 combined work experience., infrastructure, database administration, software development, business process analysis)This position is for an Epic Application Analyst to support the Outpatient Clinical Systems . This position is a Hybrid position and will require in-person work once a week and may require additional in-person work for training and other operational needs.Â SkillRequired / DesiredAmountof ExperienceCertification in EpicCare Inpatient Clinical Documentation inc. Behavioral Health, EpicCare Inpatient Order Entry inc. Provider DocumentationHighly desiredÂ Â 2 yrs. exp. in health services research &/or health policy analysisRequired2Â experience in multiple areas of assigned responsibility (infrastructure, database administration, software development, business process analysis)RequiredÂ Â Epic Willow module certificationRequiredÂ Â The Analyst in this role will primarily work with the initial implementation of the Epic System and then support the system and end user to make sure the technology is optimized for our Regional Psychiatric Hospital for enhanced work processes and overall patient care. We are a close-knit community of IT staff and develop applications which allows mental health and addiction providers to serve our community in need. Our applications support, regulate, fund, and collect data to allow our organization the ability to respond to those in crisis as well as those needing continuity of care.â€¢ In conjunction with Hospital Services, performs in-depth analysis of current and future workflows, data collection, report details and other technical issues associated with the Epic EHR and designated third-party applications.â€¢ Collects requirements regarding potential system enhancements or new system implementation and prepares details of specifications needed.â€¢ Prioritizes and implements requested changes to the system.â€¢ Investigates standardization and process improvement opportunities while making build decisions.â€¢ Validates data is accurate and meets business requirements.â€¢ Designs and executes small-scale application testing as required.â€¢ Provides support for the installation and implementation of system patches, service utilities and version upgrades as assigned.â€¢ Troubleshoots, identifies root cause and documents problems of simple to medium complexity for assigned applications and systems.â€¢ Analyzes and manages systems or third-party vendors/service providers to ensure service level agreements are met.â€¢ Maintains data integrity and security for assigned applications and systems.â€¢ Develops system documentation as assigned per standards.â€¢ Develops communication for deployments, upgrades,optimizations and other system changes as assigned.â€¢ Analyzes workflows and understanding policies, procedures and constraints in core clinical or business area(s) of responsibility.â€¢ Partners with quality, operational and business leaders on system design and optimization to meet quality, safety, financial and efficiency needs.

Job Summary: We are seeking a highly skilled NetApp Certified Resource with 6 to 8 years of experience in NetApp Storage Grid and NetApp Storage Administration. The ideal candidate will work in a hybrid model during the day shift. This role does not require travel. The candidate will be responsible for managing and analyzing geospatial data to support our company's objectives and contribute to impactful projects that benefit society.
• Manage and analyze geospatial data to support various projects and initiatives.
• Oversee the administration and maintenance of NetApp Storage Grid systems.
• Provide technical expertise in NetApp Storage Administration to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
• Develop and implement data management strategies to enhance data accessibility and usability.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate geospatial data into business processes.
• Ensure data integrity and security by implementing best practices and protocols.
• Create detailed reports and visualizations to communicate findings and insights to stakeholders.
• Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to geospatial data and storage systems.
• Stay updated with the latest advancements in geospatial technologies and storage solutions.
• Train and mentor junior team members on geospatial data management and storage administration.
• Contribute to the development of policies and procedures for data management and storage.
• Support the company's objectives by providing accurate and timely geospatial data analysis.
• Enhance the company's impact on society by leveraging geospatial data to inform decision-making.
• Possess 6 to 8 years of experience in geospatial data analysis and NetApp Storage Grid.
• Demonstrate expertise in NetApp Storage Administration with a proven track record.
• Exhibit strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
• Show proficiency in data management and visualization tools.
• Have excellent communication and collaboration abilities.
• Display a commitment to staying current with industry trends and technologies.
Years of Experience:     8.00 Years of Experience

Job Summary: We are seeking a highly skilled NetApp Certified Resource with 6 to 8 years of experience in NetApp Storage Grid and NetApp Storage Administration. The ideal candidate will work in a hybrid model during the day shift. This role does not require travel. The candidate will be responsible for managing and analyzing geospatial data to support our company's objectives and contribute to impactful projects that benefit society.
• Manage and analyze geospatial data to support various projects and initiatives.
• Oversee the administration and maintenance of NetApp Storage Grid systems.
• Provide technical expertise in NetApp Storage Administration to ensure optimal performance and reliability.
• Develop and implement data management strategies to enhance data accessibility and usability.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate geospatial data into business processes.
• Ensure data integrity and security by implementing best practices and protocols.
• Create detailed reports and visualizations to communicate findings and insights to stakeholders.
• Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to geospatial data and storage systems.
• Stay updated with the latest advancements in geospatial technologies and storage solutions.
• Train and mentor junior team members on geospatial data management and storage administration.
• Contribute to the development of policies and procedures for data management and storage.
• Support the company's objectives by providing accurate and timely geospatial data analysis.
• Enhance the company's impact on society by leveraging geospatial data to inform decision-making.
• Possess 6 to 8 years of experience in geospatial data analysis and NetApp Storage Grid.
• Demonstrate expertise in NetApp Storage Administration with a proven track record.
• Exhibit strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
• Show proficiency in data management and visualization tools.
• Have excellent communication and collaboration abilities.
• Display a commitment to staying current with industry trends and technologies.
Years of Experience:     8.00 Years of Experience

Job Title: AI/ML/LLM Engineer – AI-Assisted RTL Integration

LLM Engineer with expertise in prompt engineering, dataset creation, fine-tuning, and deployment of on-premises open-source LLMs for RTL (Register Transfer Level) design. The ideal candidate will work closely with RTL domain experts to develop and optimize AI-assisted RTL integration workflows.
The role involves prompt engineering, output validation and re-prompting, fine-tuning of LLMs when necessary, and building datasets to enhance model accuracy using the latest AI/ML technologies.

column2: • Deploy and optimize open-source LLMs on-premises for RTL integration.
• Develop custom pipelines for LLM-assisted RTL design, analysis, and verification.
• Work with RTL experts to fine-tune prompts for best performance.
• Design, refine, and test effective prompts for RTL integration tasks.
• Continuously evaluate LLM responses and develop strategies for output validation.
• Implement re-prompting techniques to improve accuracy and efficiency.
• Identify gaps in model accuracy and develop datasets for model retraining.
• Collect, clean, and curate RTL-specific datasets to improve model performance.
• Fine-tune LLMs using state-of-the-art training frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face).
• Experiment with latest AI/ML techniques to optimize LLM efficiency for RTL workflows.
• Implement evaluation metrics to measure model performance in RTL tasks.
• Conduct benchmarking and performance tuning to ensure model accuracy.
• Develop feedback loops for continuous improvement of LLM-assisted RTL processes.
• Work closely with RTL engineers to understand domain challenges.
• Stay up to date with the latest advancements in AI/ML and hardware design automation.
• Evaluate and implement state-of-the-art LLM architectures for RTL-specific applications.
• Strong expertise in LLMs – Open-source models like Llama, Falcon, Mistral, or GPT-based architectures.
• Experience in fine-tuning LLMs using PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Hugging Face.
• Prompt engineering expertise – Ability to craft optimized prompts for RTL tasks.
• Understanding of RTL design (basic knowledge preferred) and how AI can assist in hardware workflows.
• Experience in data collection, preprocessing, and synthetic dataset creation for fine-tuning.
• Familiarity with LLM inference optimization techniques (e.g., quantization, pruning).
• Strong coding skills in Python and frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex, or OpenAI APIs.
• Experience with containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and on-prem model hosting.

Job Title: AI/ML/LLM Engineer – AI-Assisted RTL Integration

LLM Engineer with expertise in prompt engineering, dataset creation, fine-tuning, and deployment of on-premises open-source LLMs for RTL (Register Transfer Level) design. The ideal candidate will work closely with RTL domain experts to develop and optimize AI-assisted RTL integration workflows.
The role involves prompt engineering, output validation and re-prompting, fine-tuning of LLMs when necessary, and building datasets to enhance model accuracy using the latest AI/ML technologies.

column2: • Deploy and optimize open-source LLMs on-premises for RTL integration.
• Develop custom pipelines for LLM-assisted RTL design, analysis, and verification.
• Work with RTL experts to fine-tune prompts for best performance.
• Design, refine, and test effective prompts for RTL integration tasks.
• Continuously evaluate LLM responses and develop strategies for output validation.
• Implement re-prompting techniques to improve accuracy and efficiency.
• Identify gaps in model accuracy and develop datasets for model retraining.
• Collect, clean, and curate RTL-specific datasets to improve model performance.
• Fine-tune LLMs using state-of-the-art training frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face).
• Experiment with latest AI/ML techniques to optimize LLM efficiency for RTL workflows.
• Implement evaluation metrics to measure model performance in RTL tasks.
• Conduct benchmarking and performance tuning to ensure model accuracy.
• Develop feedback loops for continuous improvement of LLM-assisted RTL processes.
• Work closely with RTL engineers to understand domain challenges.
• Stay up to date with the latest advancements in AI/ML and hardware design automation.
• Evaluate and implement state-of-the-art LLM architectures for RTL-specific applications.
• Strong expertise in LLMs – Open-source models like Llama, Falcon, Mistral, or GPT-based architectures.
• Experience in fine-tuning LLMs using PyTorch, TensorFlow, or Hugging Face.
• Prompt engineering expertise – Ability to craft optimized prompts for RTL tasks.
• Understanding of RTL design (basic knowledge preferred) and how AI can assist in hardware workflows.
• Experience in data collection, preprocessing, and synthetic dataset creation for fine-tuning.
• Familiarity with LLM inference optimization techniques (e.g., quantization, pruning).
• Strong coding skills in Python and frameworks like LangChain, LlamaIndex, or OpenAI APIs.
• Experience with containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and on-prem model hosting.

column9: Role: Data AnalystLocation: Raleigh, NC - HybridRequired SkillsSQLPower BI dashboards developmentMicrosoft AzurePythonJD:The Data Analyst will work in collaboration with the Data Engineer, modeling department's data and producing reports. They will systematically collect, process, and perform statistical analyses on data sets. Their responsibilities include:1. Data Cleaning and Preparation: This involves filtering the data, handling missing values, and preparing the dataset for analysis to ensure accuracy and relevance.2. Data Exploration and Analysis: Analysts use statistical tools and techniques to explore and analyze data, identifying patterns, relationships, and trends.3. Data Visualization: They create visual representations of data findings through charts, graphs, and dashboards to make the data understandable.4. Reporting: Data analysts prepare reports and presentations to communicate the insights and findings from the data to stakeholders, which can influence policy and decision-making processes.5. Collaboration: They often work with other departments to understand their data needs and help them make informed decisions based on data insights.

column1: OFSAA Developer  Tampa, FL ONSITE.,"Email from Digitive LLC You don't want to miss this. OFSAA Developer Tampa, FL ONSITE.  The OFSAA Developer is responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining Oracle Financial Services Analytical Applications (OFSAA) solutions, specifically focusing on General Ledger (GL) Reconciliation, Capital Management, and Asset Liability Management (ALM). This role involves developing technical solutions, ensuring data integrity, and supporting financial and risk management processes. What are the top 3 skills required for this role? 1. OFSAA Capital Management 2. OFSAA GL Reconciliation 3. OFSAA Regulatory Reporting OFSAA Development: â€¢ Design, configure, and implement OFSAA modules for GL Reconciliation, Capital Management, and ALM. â€¢ Develop and maintain OFSAA rules, including Transfer Pricing (FTP) and Table-to-Table (T2T) transformations. â€¢ Write and optimize PL/SQL procedures to support OFSAA functionalities. System Management: â€¢ Ensure the OFSAA system is properly configured and updated to meet business and regulatory requirements. â€¢ Provide technical support and troubleshooting for OFSAA users. â€¢ Manage and optimize OFSAA batch processes and performance. Data Management: â€¢ Manage and maintain data within the OFSAA system, ensuring data integrity and accuracy. â€¢ Extract and load data from source systems into the OFSAA platform. â€¢ Develop and implement data management processes and best practices. Capital Management: â€¢ Support the implementation and configuration of OFSAA Capital Management modules. â€¢ Assist in developing and managing capital planning processes, including stress testing and scenario analysis. â€¢ Monitor and report on capital adequacy and regulatory capital requirements. Asset Liability Management (ALM): â€¢ Implement and maintain OFSAA ALM modules to manage interest rate risk, liquidity risk, and other balance sheet risks. â€¢ Conduct ALM analysis and generate reports to support strategic decision-making. â€¢ Collaborate with treasury and finance teams to optimize asset-liability strategies. General Ledger Reconciliation: â€¢ Perform daily, monthly, and quarterly reconciliations of general ledger accounts using OFSAA. â€¢ Ensure all transactions are accurately recorded and discrepancies are resolved promptly. â€¢ Maintain detailed records of reconciliation processes and outcomes. Stakeholder Collaboration: â€¢ Work closely with IT, finance, and risk management teams to ensure seamless integration of OFSAA solutions. Provide training and support to end-users on OFSAA functionalities. Years of Experience 7-15 years hanks and Regards Rashmi Jha| Digitive LLC - eVerified Company  Create your future with us  Direct Number: 209) 437-0255 | ext 1255,  Email: rashmi@godigitive.com Referral link - https://www.godigitive.com/referrals linkedin.com/in/rashmi-jha-98083521b Digitive LLC | 301 Lennon Ln, 202 | Walnut Creek, CA 94598 US Unsubscribe | Update Profile | Constant Contact Data Notice",

Title: GCP Data Engineer
Location: Charlotte, NC

A skilled and experienced Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Data Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have a broad set of technology skills and the ability to design the right solutions using a combination of Google Cloud and third-party technologies for deployment on Google Cloud.

column2: • Design and implement data solutions on Google Cloud Platform (GCP) using services such as BigQuery, Cloud Storage, Cloud Composer, Dataflow, and Data Catalog.
• Develop software code in languages such as Python, Unix Shell, and SQL.
• Design and deploy large-scale applications in the cloud.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
• Ensure the scalability, reliability, and performance of data solutions.
• Stay updated with the latest GCP technologies and best practices.
• At least 3 years of hands-on experience with GCP cloud data implementation projects.
• Minimum 2 years of experience in developing software code in Python, Unix Shell, and SQL.
• Minimum 3 years of experience in designing and deploying large-scale applications in the cloud.
• Google Cloud Platform certification such as Cloud Data Engineer, Associate, or Architect is highly preferable.
• Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently and as part of a team.
• Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
• Experience with other cloud platforms and technologies.
• Knowledge of data security and compliance best practices.
• Familiarity with DevOps practices and tools.

column1: Premium SVOD Subscriptions Increased by 10.4% in 2024,"The Weekly Summit
Read this article on LinkedIn to join the conversation

Premium SVOD subscriptions in the U.S. increased by 10.4% in 2024, reaching just over 260 million, up from 26.5 million the previous year. Netflix holds the largest share of U.S. SVOD subscriptions at 26% (about 67.5 million subscribers), while Hulu and Paramount+ each account for 14% of the market. Total new streaming signups in 2024 outpaced cancellations, with 173.3 million additions versus 147.8 million cancellations.Â  A majority of consumers are opting for ad-supported tiers when available, with ad-supported subscriptions rising to 45% of all streaming sign-ups, up from 36% in 2023. New research reveals data that might sound like a broken record: Streaming is continuing to grow, with U.S. premium SVOD subscriptions rising 10.4% in 2024, surpassing 260 million. Netflix remains the market leader with 26% share (67.5 million subscribers), followed by Hulu and Paramount+ at 14% (36.4 million each) and Disney+ and Peacock at 13% (33.8 million) and 11% (28.6 million), respectively. And while cancellations did increase by 15.8% year-over-year, overall subscriber counts remained strong. By the end of 2024, falling churn rates stabilized around 5% â€” showing that while people may switch services, they arenâ€™t leaving streaming behind forever. Part of the reason for all that turmoil? Rising prices. The average ad-free plan now costs $14 per month, up from $11, while ad-supported plans rose to $7.50 from $6.00. As a result, more consumers are opting for those ad-supported tiers, with adoption rising from 36% to 45%. Bundling is also proving effective at retaining subscribers. The Disney+ / Max bundle holds an 80% retention rate, while the Disney Bundle (Disney+, Hulu, ESPN+) sits at 73%. These trends highlight that while consumer habits evolve, Connected TV remains a dominant and growing part of the entertainment landscape. Connected TV in the News Streamers Compete For Subscribers, Distribution And Programmatic Prowess AdExchanger TV programmers and streamers are sharing their financial report cards for last quarter â€” and the results are quite a mixed bag. 5 Misconceptions About CTV: Why Itâ€™s the New Performance PowerhouseÂ  Adweek Many consumers donâ€™t differentiate between linear and CTV â€” but if you think CTV advertising is nothing more than repurposing linear TV ads for increased exposure, think again.
This email was intended for Deepa Kiran (--Deepa)

column2: • Lead design, development, and implementation of OTM Cloud.  Oversee OTM integration and agent architecture to ensure seamless data exchange and optimize functionality to support supply chain and logistics operations. Works with IT Leads to build scalable solutions to fit current and future business requirements.
• 15+ years of experience in OTM implementations with a strong focus on solution design with at least 5 years in OTM Cloud.

Greetings for the day…!
Hope everything is going well.
This is from Sage IT Inc. I am working on an exclusive requirement, please find the below JD. If you are comfortable with Job Description, please forward your updated resume.
Position: OTM Architect Onsite (OTM On-Prem to Cloud Migration)

column2: • Lead design, development, and implementation of OTM Cloud.  Oversee OTM integration and agent architecture to ensure seamless data exchange and optimize functionality to support supply chain and logistics operations. Works with IT Leads to build scalable solutions to fit current and future business requirements.
• 15+ years of experience in OTM implementations with a strong focus on solution design with at least 5 years in OTM Cloud.
• Proven experience leading OTM On-Prem to Cloud migration projects from a vendor/implementation partner perspective.
• Deep expertise in OTM Cloud and On-Prem configurations, workflows, and business process design.

column1: Role: Lead  QA Tester
Location: Auburn Hills, MI location Onsite
Experiance: 12-15 Years
The QA Lead must follow existing standards and processes and be able to recommend/advise on best practice.
The QA Lead must be familiar with and able to lead all testing types:

Purpose of Role/Organizational Unit:  The QA Lead and QA Team are responsible for identifying and lowering risk to our business users and end consumers through robust and thorough application testing that covers all functional and non-functional requirements.
• Plays a lead role in QA efforts on multiple and simultaneous projects.
• Works on projects of moderate to high complexity that requires in-depth knowledge across multiple technical areas and business segments.
• Work with software architects and developers throughout the software development life cycle to develop software test strategy and plan.
• Responsible for leading the full test lifecycle
• Participate in all aspects of testing
• Responsible for the overall success of testing
• Manages assigned projects from IT Quality Testing through user acceptance testing and production deployment.
• Performs quality audits to ensure quality standards, procedures and methodologies are being followed.

• Advanced technical knowledge and experience is required in this environment.  The QA Lead must have hands on testing and test lead experience in new and legacy computing architectures and environments.
• The QA Lead must have a solid background in front end as well as backend testing.
• Strong ETL experience is required, with advanced SQL as well as API testing.
• Experience with leading test automation efforts.
• Experience with leading performance testing efforts.
• Strong verbal and written communications skills, with an ability to express technical concepts in business terms.
• Strong analytical, problem-solving, and conceptual skills.
• Strong teamwork and interpersonal skills.
• Thorough knowledge of QA management tools, such as JIRA.
• Knowledge of relational databases and database applications (Oracle and Big Data).
• Must be able to work on multiple complex projects, meet deadlines, and deal with conflicting priorities. Having the ability to multitask is a must.
• Strong leadership skills are required. Having the ability to work individually and within a team is must.
• Previous experience with global initiatives or projects utilizing virtual teams is required.
Educational Requirements: • A Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related discipline, or equivalent work experience is required.
Thanks & Regards
Tejaswi Athili
1908 Thomes Ave, Cheyenne, WY 82001
Email : tejaswi_athili@insoursysinc.com  Website:  www.insoursys.com

column1: Urgent Requirement || Cognos developer || Raleigh, NC,"Hi,
1. 7 to 10 years experience as a Cognos developer in multiple frame work
support, and Data modules creations using Cognos tool. 2. Hands on Cognos
development experience. Preferrable with Cognos Analytics is must. 3. Hands
on experience with Cognos Data Module & Framework Manager for analytics
projects. 4. Experience with Large Enterprise Clients such as banking domain
or insurance domain. 5. Should have Advanced knowledge of SQL for
utilization. 6. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define Bi Data
modeling like Star schema, snowflake and should have knowledge in Qlik. 7.
Analyze data-related processes and workflows to identify opportunities for
improvement and optimization.8. Communicate key data governance initiatives
and findings to stakeholders at all levels of the organization.9. Associate
should posses strong written communication and verbal communication. 10.
Associate should have strong knowledge about IDW or insurance

column1: SAP HCM/ Employee Central Payroll /SuccessFactors Consultant (Contract, New York City, NY (Local Only & Onsite),"Position:   SAP HCM/ Employee Central Payroll/SuccessFactors Consultant
Location:  New York City, NY (Local Only & Onsite)
Responsibilities to include, but not limited to:

Provide end-to-end production support for a complex union based daily payroll lifecycle environment comprising of SAP SuccessFactors Employee Central, Employee Central Payroll, and hours to gross Time Management systems with 100+ interfaces
Review periodic SAP notes/patches/HRSP, evaluate and apply to SAP SuccessFactors landscape.
Evaluate TUBs as delivered by BSI and coordinate prod deployment.
Configure, customize and implement new Payroll modules/functionality as required

Produce solution design, documentation, and successful delivery of Employee Central Payroll with expert attention to all architectural qualities for an effectively working SuccessFactors Human Resource (HCM) system.
Plan, manage, deliver, implement, support, administer and/or monitor SAP integration solutions and middleware for on-premise, cloud or hybrid scenarios
Monitor batch jobs and address production support issues
Understand business requirement, develop detailed functional design, create test plan and help production deployment
Coordinate activities of team with other teams within the IT function
Implements the solution based on functional specification and resolves issues independently in the areas of own skills.
Ensures technical objects are smoothly imported to UAT and eventually in Production by checking dependencies and sequence.
Part of development team for production support but the main focus is with Payroll functional consultation.
Minimum 8 years of experience in working with payroll/HR departments that depend on a large, complex SAP SuccessFactors Employee central payroll system.
Extensive experience in configuring and custom development with excellent ECP functional skills.
Deep knowledge on SAP EC payroll configurations, wage type setups, BSI tax setup including Tax factory and Tax Profile Factory
Hands-On experience integrating multiple systems like ADP, Bank, SAP FI, 3PR, and PCC functionalities
Demonstrated ability in understanding of the Payroll & HR business area(s) including related policies, procedures, and specific business practices
Experience in working with HCM, FI RICEF objects.
Experience applying HRSP and BSI updates and patches to SuccessFactors ECP applications.
Knowledge of the SuccessFactors HXM suite of application, Payroll Command Center and EC to ECP replication
Ability to write functional specifications, program, test, and manage the transition of modifications through the quality assurance and change control process
Experience working with GL integration with multiple ERP finance systems including ECC, and Oracle EBS
Good knowledge about the Benefits Module, Time Management, Payroll Related Info types, Payroll status record, Payroll control record, posting data to FI.
Working knowledge in all SAP development tools and methodologies, including ABAP workbench, BAPI/IDOC, ALE, Reports, Workflow, Smartforms, ABAP upgrade, enhancement technique.
Bachelors degree in Computer Science or equivalent
Knowledge of union payroll is preferred
Proficiency in SAP security and basis admin function
Demonstrated problem solving skills, as well as continuous process improvement skills
Strong understanding of software development life cycle
Strong communication and inter personal skills
Ability to work independently, to prioritize tasks effectively in a collaborative environment with shared resources
SAP certification is a big plus

The Senior ERP Specialist plays a critical role in the technical administration and enhancement of ERP applications across multiple modules and integrations. This position is essential for ensuring that the ERP environment operates efficiently, meets quality standards, and aligns with business objectives. The specialist will drive continuous improvements and optimizations while effectively managing software updates and troubleshooting complex issues.

1. Manage The Overall Erp Environment, Including Configurations, and Integrations in Modules Such as Finance, Supply Chain, And Manufacturing, Ensuring Optimal Performance and Compliance with Best Practices.

2. Monitor And Assess New Software Releases, Support Packs, And Kernel Upgrades for Their Impact on Application Performance and User Experience, Implementing Necessary Adjustments to Maintain System Integrity.
3. Identify And Implement Opportunities for Improvement and Optimization Within the Erp System by Analyzing Business Processes and Aligning Enhancements With Organizational Goals.
4. Perform Advanced Troubleshooting for Complex Technical Issues at Both the ERP and Database Levels, Utilizing Tools Such as SQL And System Logs to Diagnose and Resolve Problems Efficiently.
5. Stay Updated on Emerging Erp Technology Trends and Best Practices, Transferring Knowledge to Team Members Through Workshops and Documentation to Enhance Team Capabilities.
1. Expert Level Proficiency in Erp Data Management, With A Strong Understanding of ERP Architecture and Multi-Module Integration.
2. Excellent Troubleshooting Skills, With In-Depth Knowledge of SQL Databases and Performance Tuning.
3. Strong Analytical Skills to Identify Optimization Opportunities Within Erp Systems.
4. Familiarity With Software Release Management and The Implications of Updates On Existing Configurations.
Optional But Valuable Certifications: SAP Certified Technology Associate, Oracle Erp Cloud Certification, or Microsoft Dynamics 365 Certification.
This demand is for Data cloud admin (Salesforce)
Key responsibilities in a Salesforce Data Cloud role:
- Data Source Integration: Connect and extract data from various systems like CRM, ERP, marketing automation platforms, and external data sources.
- Data Mapping and Transformation: Map data fields from different sources to a unified schema, performing necessary data cleansing and normalization.
- Data Modeling: Design data models within the Data Cloud to create a comprehensive customer view, including relationships between different data entities.
- Data Quality Management: Implement data quality checks and validation rules to ensure data accuracy and consistency.
- Data Governance: Define and enforce data access controls, data retention policies, and data usage guidelines.
- Solution Design: Collaborate with business users to understand their data needs and design customized Data Cloud solutions.
- Implementation and Deployment: Build and deploy Data Cloud solutions, including data pipelines, data flows, and data transformations.
- User Training and Support: Provide training and support to end users on how to access and utilize data within the Data Cloud.
Skills needed for Salesforce Data Cloud jobs:
- Strong understanding of data integration principles and technologies
- Expertise in data modeling and database design
- Proficiency in data cleansing and quality techniques
- Knowledge of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes
- Experience with Salesforce platform and APIs
- Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work with cross-functional teams
- Experience with Azure is also a nice to have
Thanks & Regards
Sharmila Shaik
Yochana Solutions INC
Sharmila@yochana.com

The Senior ERP Specialist plays a critical role in the technical administration and enhancement of ERP applications across multiple modules and integrations. This position is essential for ensuring that the ERP environment operates efficiently, meets quality standards, and aligns with business objectives. The specialist will drive continuous improvements and optimizations while effectively managing software updates and troubleshooting complex issues.

1. Manage The Overall Erp Environment, Including Configurations, and Integrations in Modules Such as Finance, Supply Chain, And Manufacturing, Ensuring Optimal Performance and Compliance with Best Practices.

2. Monitor And Assess New Software Releases, Support Packs, And Kernel Upgrades for Their Impact on Application Performance and User Experience, Implementing Necessary Adjustments to Maintain System Integrity.
3. Identify And Implement Opportunities for Improvement and Optimization Within the Erp System by Analyzing Business Processes and Aligning Enhancements With Organizational Goals.
4. Perform Advanced Troubleshooting for Complex Technical Issues at Both the ERP and Database Levels, Utilizing Tools Such as SQL And System Logs to Diagnose and Resolve Problems Efficiently.
5. Stay Updated on Emerging Erp Technology Trends and Best Practices, Transferring Knowledge to Team Members Through Workshops and Documentation to Enhance Team Capabilities.
1. Expert Level Proficiency in Erp Data Management, With A Strong Understanding of ERP Architecture and Multi-Module Integration.
2. Excellent Troubleshooting Skills, With In-Depth Knowledge of SQL Databases and Performance Tuning.
3. Strong Analytical Skills to Identify Optimization Opportunities Within Erp Systems.
4. Familiarity With Software Release Management and The Implications of Updates On Existing Configurations.
Optional But Valuable Certifications: SAP Certified Technology Associate, Oracle Erp Cloud Certification, or Microsoft Dynamics 365 Certification.
This demand is for Data cloud admin (Salesforce)
Key responsibilities in a Salesforce Data Cloud role:
- Data Source Integration: Connect and extract data from various systems like CRM, ERP, marketing automation platforms, and external data sources.
- Data Mapping and Transformation: Map data fields from different sources to a unified schema, performing necessary data cleansing and normalization.
- Data Modeling: Design data models within the Data Cloud to create a comprehensive customer view, including relationships between different data entities.
- Data Quality Management: Implement data quality checks and validation rules to ensure data accuracy and consistency.
- Data Governance: Define and enforce data access controls, data retention policies, and data usage guidelines.
- Solution Design: Collaborate with business users to understand their data needs and design customized Data Cloud solutions.
- Implementation and Deployment: Build and deploy Data Cloud solutions, including data pipelines, data flows, and data transformations.
- User Training and Support: Provide training and support to end users on how to access and utilize data within the Data Cloud.
Skills needed for Salesforce Data Cloud jobs:
- Strong understanding of data integration principles and technologies
- Expertise in data modeling and database design
- Proficiency in data cleansing and quality techniques
- Knowledge of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes
- Experience with Salesforce platform and APIs
- Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work with cross-functional teams
- Experience with Azure is also a nice to have
Thanks & Regards
Sharmila Shaik
Yochana Solutions INC
Sharmila@yochana.com

The Senior ERP Specialist plays a critical role in the technical administration and enhancement of ERP applications across multiple modules and integrations. This position is essential for ensuring that the ERP environment operates efficiently, meets quality standards, and aligns with business objectives. The specialist will drive continuous improvements and optimizations while effectively managing software updates and troubleshooting complex issues.

1. Manage The Overall Erp Environment, Including Configurations, and Integrations in Modules Such as Finance, Supply Chain, And Manufacturing, Ensuring Optimal Performance and Compliance with Best Practices.

2. Monitor And Assess New Software Releases, Support Packs, And Kernel Upgrades for Their Impact on Application Performance and User Experience, Implementing Necessary Adjustments to Maintain System Integrity.
3. Identify And Implement Opportunities for Improvement and Optimization Within the Erp System by Analyzing Business Processes and Aligning Enhancements With Organizational Goals.
4. Perform Advanced Troubleshooting for Complex Technical Issues at Both the ERP and Database Levels, Utilizing Tools Such as SQL And System Logs to Diagnose and Resolve Problems Efficiently.
5. Stay Updated on Emerging Erp Technology Trends and Best Practices, Transferring Knowledge to Team Members Through Workshops and Documentation to Enhance Team Capabilities.
1. Expert Level Proficiency in Erp Data Management, With A Strong Understanding of ERP Architecture and Multi-Module Integration.
2. Excellent Troubleshooting Skills, With In-Depth Knowledge of SQL Databases and Performance Tuning.
3. Strong Analytical Skills to Identify Optimization Opportunities Within Erp Systems.
4. Familiarity With Software Release Management and The Implications of Updates On Existing Configurations.
Optional But Valuable Certifications: SAP Certified Technology Associate, Oracle Erp Cloud Certification, or Microsoft Dynamics 365 Certification.
This demand is for Data cloud admin (Salesforce)
Key responsibilities in a Salesforce Data Cloud role:
- Data Source Integration: Connect and extract data from various systems like CRM, ERP, marketing automation platforms, and external data sources.
- Data Mapping and Transformation: Map data fields from different sources to a unified schema, performing necessary data cleansing and normalization.
- Data Modeling: Design data models within the Data Cloud to create a comprehensive customer view, including relationships between different data entities.
- Data Quality Management: Implement data quality checks and validation rules to ensure data accuracy and consistency.
- Data Governance: Define and enforce data access controls, data retention policies, and data usage guidelines.
- Solution Design: Collaborate with business users to understand their data needs and design customized Data Cloud solutions.
- Implementation and Deployment: Build and deploy Data Cloud solutions, including data pipelines, data flows, and data transformations.
- User Training and Support: Provide training and support to end users on how to access and utilize data within the Data Cloud.
Skills needed for Salesforce Data Cloud jobs:
- Strong understanding of data integration principles and technologies
- Expertise in data modeling and database design
- Proficiency in data cleansing and quality techniques
- Knowledge of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes
- Experience with Salesforce platform and APIs
- Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work with cross-functional teams
- Experience with Azure is also a nice to have
Thanks & Regards
Sharmila Shaik
Yochana Solutions INC
Sharmila@yochana.com

column1: We are seeking a Data Architect with expertise in Risk & Compliance, Sanctions Screening, and Anti-Money Laundering (AML) to lead the design and development of scalable data solutions that support financial crime detection and regulatory compliance. This role requires a strong architectural mindset to design high-performance data platforms, optimize data pipelines, and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements. The ideal candidate should have deep experience with big data architectures, cloud platforms, and data security best practices while collaborating with cross-functional teams.

column2: Define and implement end-to-end data architecture for risk and compliance systems, ensuring scalability, security, and performance.
Design data models, pipelines, and frameworks to support sanctions screening, AML transaction monitoring, KYC, fraud analytics, and regulatory reporting.
Develop high-availability and fault-tolerant data processing architectures that handle large-scale, real-time financial transactions.
Architect and implement big data solutions using Apache Spark, Hadoop, Databricks, or Snowflake.
Leverage cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) for data storage, transformation, and analytics, integrating services like AWS Glue, Redshift, Synapse, or BigQuery.

Optimize query performance, indexing strategies, and distributed computing for large-scale datasets.
Automate ETL/ELT pipelines, data validation, and reconciliation processes to improve efficiency and accuracy.

Work closely with Risk, Compliance, AML, and Fraud teams to define data requirements and align technology solutions with business objectives.
Manage the product backlog through execution and delivery.
Guide and mentor data engineers, ensuring best practices in data architecture, engineering, and security.
Engage with executive leadership and stakeholders, providing technical recommendations and strategic insights.

This is Priyanshu from Shef Solutions. Hope you are doing Well; I have a job position for you.
Job Title: Helpdesk Analyst
Location: San Francisco, CA (Onsite)
Here is What You Can Expect on a Typical Day:
· Resolves technical issues from incoming hardware/software incidents for onsite and remote users.
· Provides assistance with conference room technology (pre-meeting testing and in-meeting troubleshooting)
· Assists with device installation or moves (disconnect/reconnect), managed print setup and troubleshooting, mobile device configuration and troubleshooting
· Documents and tracks status of client inquiries, coordinates appropriate response and follows up to ensure client satisfaction.
· Exercises judgment within defined procedures and practices to determine appropriate action, escalates as necessary.
· Strong knowledge of diagnostic tools (Splunk, Aternity, NexThink) and ticketing applications (ServiceNow)
· Proficiency with computer software and hardware

· Ability to troubleshoot client problems by identifying the symptoms, reviewing documentation, asking smart questions, consulting technical partners as needed, with the goal of quickly resolving the reported issue and following up to ensure long term success of the solution.
· Ability to use remote access tools to interact with client's computer, search through files and install software drivers to resolve issues

· Experience or familiarity in using modern programming languages such as Python, Powershell, and APIs to gather device information and use this information to proactively address compliance issues on devices, automate administrative tasks and provide on demand troubleshooting scripts.

column9: Job Title: Senior Database Architect & ModelerLocation: San Antonio, TX or Plano, TX (On-site Preferred)Â Client â€“ IBM/USAAÂ Detail JD listed below:-Â We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Senior Database Architect & Modeler to join our team as we migrate our insurance application to a cloud-based Guidewire platform. This platform will support millions of users, and we need a leader who can set database standards, ensure best practices, and support scalability, maintainability, and performance across the system. This role is a unique blend of Database Administration (DBA) and Data Modeler , requiring expertise in both 3NF normalization and dimensional modeling. You will work closely with software/data engineers to ensure consistency in database design and implementation, troubleshoot performance issues, and support the migration to production environments.Â Key Responsibilities:Database Standards & Best Practices: Establish and enforce database design standards, ensuring consistency, scalability, and maintainability across the platform.Development Support: Lead database-related aspects of the development in Guidewire platform, ensuring high availability, low latency and scalability.Performance Optimization: Identify and resolve database performance issues, ensuring the platform can handle millions of users.Collaboration with Engineers: Work closely with software/data engineers to ensure database standards are adhered to during development and migration.Data Modeling: Design and implement 3NF normalization models and dimensional models.Cloud Database Expertise: Work with cloud-based databases such as Aurora PostgreSQL and analytical platforms like Snowflake.Production Support: Provide hands-on support during production outages, troubleshooting issues, and ensuring system stability.Â Qualifications:Â Experience:Â  - 10+ years of experience in database architecture, modeling, and administration.Â  - Successfully led 3+ large-scale database projects, covering the key responsibilities outlined above.Â  - Extensive experience with 3NF normalization (dozens of projects) and dimensional modeling (2+ projects).Â  - Hands-on experience with operational databases like Aurora PostgreSQL and analytical databases like Snowflake.Â  - Proven track record of working with large engineering teams in a fast-paced environment.Â Technical Skills:Â  - Strong knowledge of relational databases, cloud-based databases, and data modeling concepts.Â  - Familiarity with ETL development and data integration processes.Â  - Experience working with modeling tools like ErwinÂ  - Experience working with database monitoring tools like Datadog.Â  - Experience with SaaS platforms like Guidewire platform is a plusÂ Soft Skills:Â  - Excellent communication and collaboration skills.Â  - Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to troubleshoot complex database issues.Â Preferred Qualifications:- Experience in the insurance or financial services industry.- Familiarity with Agile/Scrum methodologies.Â - Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines, DevOps- Familiarity with metadata management tools- Familiarity with event streaming platforms like Kafka.- Familiarity with modeling for structured and semi-structured data.- Certifications in cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, etc.) or database technologies.

I have a position with our client for the below requirement, please let me know if you are interested with your Updated resume.
Position: Lead Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Data Engineer
JOB DESCRIPTION:

A skilled and experienced Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Data Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have a broad set of technology skills and the ability to design the right solutions using a combination of Google Cloud and third-party technologies for deployment on Google Cloud.
Design and implement data solutions on Google Cloud Platform (GCP) using services such as BigQuery, Cloud Storage, Cloud Composer, Dataflow, and Data Catalog.
Develop software code in languages such as Python, Unix Shell, and SQL.
Design and deploy large-scale applications in the cloud.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
Ensure the scalability, reliability, and performance of data solutions.
Stay updated with the latest GCP technologies and best practices.
At least 3 years of hands-on experience with GCP cloud data implementation projects.
Minimum 2 years of experience in developing software code in Python, Unix Shell, and SQL.
Minimum 3 years of experience in designing and deploying large-scale applications in the cloud.
Google Cloud Platform certification such as Cloud Data Engineer, Associate, or Architect is highly preferable.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently and as part of a team.
Experience with other cloud platforms and technologies.
Knowledge of data security and compliance best practices.
Thanks and regards,
