If the candidate is not local, travel covered by Capgemini.Â  If travel is involved and after selection the candidate declines the offer, costs will be paid by vendor and not Capgemini.""Â  Â  Â JOB DESCRIPTION:Â Â Â  Â  Â ""Job Description/Role Notes""""The main duty of Power BI lead manage the customer andÂ  to convert raw data into meaningful analysis with the help of interactive, easy-to-understand dashboards and reports.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Need to have good understanding on Agile methodologies and exposure/ workingÂ  with Jira (JQL)â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Build automated reports and dashboards with the help of Power BI and other reporting tools.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Understand business requirements to set functional specifications for reporting applications.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Be experienced in tools and systems on MS SQL Server BI Stack, including TSQL, Power Query, MDX, PowerBIâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Needs to have good knowledge of PowerBI visualization such as Bar, stacked charts, line charts, PI charts, Area charts, Slicers, tables and matrix.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Needs to have good knowledge of DAX. Better if they are aware of contexts and context transitions. Usage of calculate, filter, aggregate and iterative functions will be good.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Be able to quickly shape data into reporting and analytics solutions.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Have knowledge of database fundamentals such as multidimensional database design, relational database design, and more.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â It will be good if they have experience of connecting to multiple data sources such as SQL, CSV, JSON, Cloud services and SharePoint.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Experience with PowerBI service is expected. Good if awareness of scheduling refresh is there.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Should have experience in creating relationships in PowerBI desktop.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Power BI Developer Responsibilitiesâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â The following are the various responsibilities of Power BI developer:â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To understand business requirements in the BI context and design data models to convert raw data to meaningful insights.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To create dashboards and visual interactive reports using Power BIâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To identify KPIs with clear objectives and monitor them consistently.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To analyze data and present it through reports that can help in decision-making.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To be able to convert business requirements into technical specifications and decide the timeline to accomplish tasks.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To design, develop, and deploy Power BI scripts and perform efficient detailed analysis.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To perform DAX queries and functions in Power BIâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To create charts and document data with algorithms, parameters, models, and relations explanationsâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To conduct data warehouse developmentâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To perform SQL querying for best resultsâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To use filters and graphs for a better understanding of the dataâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â To make technical changes to existing BI systems in order to enhance their functioning.Power BI Developer SkillsPower BI developer should have business intelligence, data science, and data analytics skills with prior knowledge in data integration, data modeling, data warehousing, and presentation concepts.The following are some of the required skills for Power BI developer:â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Need to have good understanding on Agile methodologies and exposure/ workingÂ  with Jira (JQL) is mustâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â BI tools: Skills in BI tools and BI systems, such as Power BI, etc., creating data-rich dashboards, implementing Row-level Security (RLS) in Power BI, writing DAX expressions, etc.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Experience in data-specific roles: A minimum experience of two or three years of experience working with BI tools or any data-specific role with a sound knowledge of database management, data modeling, business intelligence, SQL querying, data warehousing, and online analytical processing (OLAP)â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Microsoft BI stack: In-depth understanding and experience with Microsoft BI stacks such as Power Pivot, Power BIâ€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Data analytics: The ability to drill down on data and visualize it in the best possible way through charts, reports, or dashboards.â€¢Â  Â  Â  Â Software development skills: Understanding of software development architecture and technical aspects.""""Â

This is Vishal Holge from Agile Enterprise Solutions Inc

The AOC is seeking proposals from prospective Offerors to provide two (2) Senior Software Engineers. The Senior Software Engineers will play a crucial role in designing, developing, and maintaining two of our primary applications being rewritten. The focus areas include event-driven design, Spring Boot, microservices architecture, Kubernetes, React, Elastic search, and either RabbitMQ or Kafka.
a.          Bachelor’s degree in computer science or a related field (as determined by the AOC).
b.          Create responsive user interfaces using React.
c.          Apply event-driven design principles to build scalable and resilient applications.
d.          Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design and implement software solutions.
b.          Work with RabbitMQ for message queuing and event streaming.
c.           If the experience is in Kafka, understand the architectural differences between RabbitMQ and  Kafka.
c.          Deploy Microservices to Kubernetes clusters, utilizing CI/CD pipeline.
a.          Conduct system testing and debugging activities.
b.          Write unit tests with a goal of 85% coverage and participate in peer code reviews.
a. The design shall include sequence diagram for major use cases.
b.          Document technical specifications, architecture, and design decisions.
c.     Collaborate with product managers, designers, and other engineers to define requirements and deliverables.
a.  A weekly report communicating project progress and status. The AOC will provide the reporting format to the Successful Proposed Resource.
b.. The resource will report activity every week to communicate progress made on the programs/projects.
c. Weekly time reporting on JIS provided forms and any additional reports as assigned by the supervising manager.
(1)        Analyze complex technical challenges and propose effective solutions.
Agile Enterprise Solutions Inc || ""Ensuring Client's Success""||
www.aesinc.us.com

column9: HiHope you are doing well !!I have an urgent position. Kindly go through the Job description and let me know if this would be of interest to you.Role : Senior BI Architect (Hybrid)Location:Â Atlanta, GA - 2 days a week onsite (Local only)Duration : 6+ monthsJob Description:Note : Must have legit LinkedIn profile.BI Senior Managing Architect: The successful candidate should have a strong background in data management, data warehousing, BI, and Analytics. You will have the opportunity to teach and inspire the people around you, present your findings to senior stakeholders and help shape the company's digital future. Teamwork, influence, stakeholder management and collaboration are key to the role. Communicating at the right level is vital, and your day-to-day stakeholder map will range from C Suite to directors to developers.You will work closely with the Director of Digital Insights and Analytics to bring full suite of reporting and insights for our digital customer platform. You will help us build and execute various strategies and solutions related to collecting and organizing data from digital commerce and customer platform, enabling reporting on digital commerce and customer platform (Salesforce), as well as on centralized data warehouse platform (Snowflake). You will generate insights from customer transactions, digital marketing campaigns, and inform several customer-related strategies.Success will require a team member with a consultative nature, strong customer service focus, passion for building relationships and presenting concepts to others, and the ability to effectively articulate complex technical situations to business users. The role is a key intermediary between business teams and technical developers and must have a thorough understanding of BI concepts and tools. Attention to detail and experience in data analysis will help to ensure the overall quality of our program.Key Responsibilities:Partnering with Digital insights manager to Develop, manage, and update our digital analytics strategy.Provide Business Intelligence leadership, subject matter expertise, vision and life cycle management for ensuring our digital commerce approach is Data-driven.Steward CONA BI and Data Warehouse development and governance principlesKPIs, PowerBI Scorecards, Bottler-specific analysis in support of routine Bottler Engagement (weekly, monthly), on-demand Bottler-specific analysisDriving adoption of the available tools with key stakeholders / bottlersMake data available for self-service analysis and reporting for Bottlers.Ensure data is of top quality thatâ€™s certified and trusted.Ensure data can be fully explained from source (app where its created) to KPIs or insights that are being served up through reporting or in self-service data modelGenerate requested insights, as well Proactively generate insights to inform platform strategies.Work closely with BI developers and support team to ensure all aspects of Data lifecycle â€“ sourcing, organization, reports, metric and insights - are working seamlessWhat makes you a good fit?Experienced in Data management and Business intelligenceFlexible and comfortable using a range of DW platforms and BI tools & techniquesExpertise in managing ELT processes, extracting data into staging layers and transforming/modeling into functional tablesAbility to explain how metrics are calculated and how business processes affect metrics.Good understanding of business processes, applications and data structures within Customer spaceAble to engage others and can flex communication style for the audience.Strong collaborator, focused on the customer and business outcomesSelf-starter, proactive, an explorerSomeone who shares knowledge and loves to help others.Able to balance customer and business performance outcomes, prioritizing accordinglyA proven track record of continued high performance with increasing product management and people leadership responsibility that is recognized internally and by the bottler communityProven ability to lead, influence and collaborate effectively with cross-functional teamsVisionary, strategic thinking, and problem-solving skillsAbility to balance high customer focused orientation and service attitude with strategic long-term plansStrong ability to influence at a senior exec level, articulate well and communicate effectivelyRequirements:5+ years of experience working with customer solutions (Web, Field Service, Sales force automation, Sales Execution, Planning & Forecasting, CRM etc.)5+ years of proven experience in an analyst role3+ years of managing projects (Business requirements gathering, Design, Delivery & support)2+ years of leadership experienceBachelorâ€™s degree or higher in Business intelligence, Business analyst, Business, or a similar fieldExpertise in using Data warehousing platforms like Snowflake, SQL, etc. and Data visualization solutions like Tableau and PowerBIUnderstanding of Salesforce platform, Data structures, and Data integration methods would be a plusExpert knowledge of MS Office programs with focus on PowerPoint and ExcelBasic knowledge of SQL and/or PythonIf you are interested, please share your updated resume and suggest the best number & time to connect with you.Thanks & RegardsHimanshu GuptaUS IT RECRUITER,Â DMS VISIONS INC(972) 433-0229 Ext-104Â |Â Â dmsvisions.comhimanshu@dmsvisions.comLinkedIn:Â linkedin.com/in/himanshu-gupta-1888a12074645 Avon Lane, Suite 210, Frisco, TX 75033Â

column9: Hi,Â Greetings from Smart IT Frame, Hope you are doing well!!!Â Role: Windows L4 ArchitectLocation: Raritan, NJ (Onsite)Duration: ContractJob Description:We are seeking a service-minded Senior Windows Engineer (L4) with specialized expertise in supporting shared shopfloor endpoints. This role is crucial for overseeing and modernizing endpoint management across a global, regulated pharmaceutical and medical devices environment. The focus is on managing Windows 10 and Windows 11 endpoints, including complex Operational Technology systems, and driving the transition from legacy (SCCM, GPOs) to modern (Intune, Autopilot, Entra) solutions. The ideal candidate will demonstrate a data-driven mindset, excel in cross-functional collaboration, and be comfortable providing final-tier (L4) escalation support for critical Windows issues. Experience with Linux (Ubuntu) at an L2 level, Tableau reporting, and IT support in manufacturing or lab environments is a strong plus.Â Key ResponsibilitiesÂ 1. Windows Engineering & Troubleshooting (L4)Serve as the final escalation point for complex endpoint and OS issues in a large-scale enterprise.Troubleshoot interactions between Windows devices, networks, firewalls, and Active Directory.Collaborate with cross-functional teams (network, AD, InfoSec, etc.) to ensure seamless system performance.Â 2. Endpoint Management & ModernizationGovern enterprise endpoints using SCCM, Intune, Autopilot, and Entra, ensuring security and compliance.Maintain and optimize Group Policy Objects (GPOs), leading the transition from traditional to modern management practices.Oversee basic deployment and reporting tasks through SCCM, leveraging data-driven analysis for continuous improvement.Â 3. Cloud & Virtual DesktopDeploy and support Windows 365 or Azure Virtual Desktop solutions.Integrate zero-trust frameworks and security baselines in partnership with InfoSec.Â 4. Provisioning & AutomationOversee imaging and deployments for both traditional (SCCM, GPO) and modern (Intune, Autopilot) provisioning methods.Develop PowerShell scripts and other automation tools to streamline processes and reduce errors.Â 5. Regulatory Compliance & ITILOperate under GxP guidelines, ensuring strict adherence to documentation and validation requirements.Follow ITIL best practices (Change, Incident, Request, Problem, Knowledge) in ServiceNow or similar ITSM platforms.Â 6. IT Support in Manufacturing/OT EnvironmentsProvide hands-on and remote support within manufacturing and Operational Technology (OT) settings.Focus on supporting shared manufacturing systems, which are critical to production and not typical end-user systems.Ensure alignment with pharmaceutical compliance and safety protocols.Â 7. Reporting & AnalyticsUtilize Tableau or similar BI tools to create data visualizations and actionable insights.Communicate findings to stakeholders, championing a data-driven mindset across the organization.Â 8. Collaboration & Continuous ImprovementPartner with global and regional teams to standardize endpoint management processes.Identify opportunities to enhance reliability, security, and user experience through technology and process innovation.Embrace emerging technologies and champion an automation-first culture.Â Qualifications & Requirements:Bachelorâ€™s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field (or equivalent experience).8+ yearsÂ of hands-on experience in Windows engineering in large, enterprise-scale environments.Proven track record resolving complex OS, network, and infrastructure challenges.Experience supporting shared OT systems.Technical ProficiencyExpert in SCCM, Intune, Autopilot, Entra, and Active Directory/GPO management.Familiarity with Windows 365 or Azure Virtual Desktop solutions.Strong PowerShell scripting or comparable automation skills.Competency in BI tools for reporting.Knowledge of networking and firewall fundamentals.Regulatory & ITIL KnowledgeGxP or other regulated-industry experience strongly preferred.Practical exposure to ITIL frameworks and ServiceNow (or similar ITSM) tools.Â Â Soft Skills:Service-Minded Approach: Demonstrated commitment to high-quality customer support.Data-Driven Mindset: Analytical approach for continuous process improvement.Communication: Excellent verbal and written skillsÂ for both technical and non-technical audiences.Collaboration: Skilled at partnering with cross-functional teams, including manufacturing/OT areas.Adaptability: Openness to new technologies, methods, and best practices.

Identity & Access Management Analyst (RACF Administrator) onsite role   Certification is mandatory,Hi

Hope you are doing great!!Please find the requirement below , if you find yourself comfortable with the requirement please reply with your updated resume and I will get back to you or I would really appreciate if you can give me a call back at my contact number 408-317-0856 x171.
Job Titleâ€‚               â€‚â€‚         Identity & Access Management Analyst (RACF Administrator) onsite role
Project Locationâ€‚    â€‚      NY-New York/New York City
****PLEASE NOTE THIS POSITION PRIMARILY REQUIRE CONSULTANT TO WORK ONSITE. POTENTIALLY EVLOVE TO ONE (1) REMOTE DAY***
Certifications: CISSP, CISM, CRISC, or RACF-specific security certifications. ANY ONE IS MANDATORY
We're looking for an experienced IAM Security Administrator with RACF experience to lead security hardening efforts and IAM governance initiatives.
This role combines technical expertise, project leadership, and strategic alignment with business and compliance requirements.
Youâ€™ll drive remediation efforts, FIDO2 authentication rollout, identity governance enhancements, and business process alignment while ensuring the identity security.
Â· Lead mainframe security remediation efforts, identifying and mitigating risks within RACF and IAM environments.
Â· Enhance mainframe security controls, including enforcing Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) and password complexity policies for high-security applications.
Â· Oversee identity governance initiatives, ensuring compliance with industry regulations (NIST, ISO 27001, SOX, HIPAA).
Â· Utilize Vanguard Security Suite to generate audit reports, analyze access violations, and implement remediation strategies.
Â· Manage IAM projects related to FIDO2 authentication rollout, privileged access management (PAM), and risk mitigation.
Â· Work closely with IT, compliance, and security teams to align business processes with IAM best practices.
Â· Benchmark risk management practices in the transportation and government sectors to refine security frameworks.
Â· Collaborate with service providers and vendors to ensure IAM solutions align with business needs.
Â· Develop and maintain policies related to role-based access control (RBAC), access certifications, and risk assessments.
Â· Assist in application security vulnerability assessments for new and existing mainframe/RACF applications.
Â· Experience in RACF security hardening, remediation, and risk mitigation.
Â· Strong IAM knowledge, including role-based access control (RBAC), privileged access management (PAM), and identity governance.
Â· Hands-on experience with FIDO2 authentication, MFA implementation, and password policy enforcement.
Â· Experience in Vanguard Security Suite for security auditing and compliance reporting.
Â· Strong understanding of compliance frameworks (NIST, ISO 27001, PCI) and best security practices.
Â· Experience leading IAM projects and collaborating with cross-functional teams to align security initiatives with business processes.
Â· Excellent communication and project management skills, with experience working with service providers and vendors.
Â· Ability to monitor and enforce risk mitigation strategies, working closely with compliance, IT leadership, and security teams.
â€¢ Certifications: CISSP, CISM, CRISC, or RACF-specific security certifications.
â€¢ Experience integrating mainframe security with IAM solutions such as SailPoint, Okta, or Microsoft Entra ID.
â€¢ Background in government or transportation IT security is a plus.
â€¢ Hands-on experience with automation tools for security monitoring and compliance reporting.
Mainframe Security RACF Administration & Security Hardening 10/10 Advanced
Identity & Access Management (IAM) Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) & Password Policies for RACF 9/10 Advanced
Audit & Compliance Vanguard Security Suite for Reporting & Risk Analysis 9/10 Advanced
Project Leadership Leading Security Hardening & IAM Projects 8/10 Proficient
Communication & Vendor Management Stakeholder Collaboration & Service Provider Oversight 8/10 Proficient
5201 Great America Parkway Suite 320, Santa Clara CA 95054

Core Technologies:? Mobile: Strong skills in React Native with Expo + EAS for cross-platform iOS and Android apps.? Web: Proficiency in React with Vite and Tailwind CSS, emphasizing responsive web development to create adaptive, mobile-friendly web interfaces.? Technical Skills:? Deep knowledge of TypeScript for building type-safe, maintainable codebases across mobile and responsive web platforms.? Experience with ESLint for linting, Jest for testing, MobX State Trees for state management, and Storybook for developing and testing responsive UI components.? Ability to pull designs from Figma and implement them accurately, ensuring responsiveness for web applications.? Proficiency with Postman for API testing, Reactotron for debugging React Native, and Android Studio and Xcode for platform-specific development, alongside skills in responsive web debugging.? Comfort using VSCode or IntelliJ as the primary development environment.Job Specific Skills and Abilities (KSAs):? Familiarity with native mobile languages like Swift, Objective-C, Kotlin, or Java.? Experience with high-traffic, scalable applications, including responsive web systems.? Knowledge of accessibility standards (e.g., WCAG) to enhance responsive web usability.? Previous work on payment systems or public sector projects.Â

practical experience in the areas identified with specific examples.

Data Warehouse in the Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, Oracle Autonomous Data
- Reviews existing architecture and provides solution recommendations
- Develops, tests, and implements scripts/jobs for data Extract
Transform and Load (ETL) from data source(s) to target(s) in the data
- Design, develop, and optimize ETL processes using Oracle tools and
- Create and maintain data pipelines to extract data from various
sources, transform it according to business rules, and load it into Oracle
- Collaborate with data analysts and business stakeholders to understand

- Troubleshoot and resolve data quality issues and performance
- Document ETL processes, data mappings, and data lineage
- Implement data quality checks and validation procedures
- Participate in code reviews and adhere to best practices in ETL

experience in database design, development, and warehouse architecture
supportive of key duties/responsibilities identified above in an Oracle

ETL development activities in a Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse in a
- 5 years experience performing development in Oracle data warehouses
- Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work effectively
with technical stakeholders and team members.
- Proficient with various Oracle tools used to perform ETL, performance
management, and tuning for an Oracle Data Warehouse and Oracle Cloud
- Strong proficiency in Oracle Database, PL/SQL, and SQL

- Solid understanding of data warehousing concepts and dimensional
- Familiarity with Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Edition

team including but not limited to data modeling, requirements solicitation,

column1: • Assist in creating and running the cutover plan.
• Assist with testing Oracle Financial Modules along with the edge systems.

This position plays a key role in validating financial data from legacy applications into modern applications such as Oracle Fusion.

column2: • Data Validation
• Requirement validation
• Test scenario formation and execution
• Understanding and performing business processes in multiple application technologies
• Ensure requirement specification is aligned with industry standards and best practices
• Project management using established PMO processes and documentation
• Facilitation of Testing,
• Assisting with Coordination of the Production Cutover Process, Post Production Support turnover, and business interaction to ensure a smooth production transition
• Leading project teams through the project management process, adhering to standards, processes, and documentation put forth by a PMO
• Experience Required:  9-14 Years
• Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, accounting or related field.
• Minimum 5+ years of experience in a finance role.
• Functional knowledge of Oracle Financials modules (version R12 or fusion), with some knowledge of Financial Analysis, Financial Consolidation, and other Financial Reporting Systems.

• Proven knowledge of Finance business processes in a large corporate finance global environment, as it relates to the Oracle Financials, and Financial Analysis and Consolidation/Planning systems, with an emphasis on Oracle Financials as well as thorough awareness of trends and developments of emerging technologies, evaluating all for appropriateness and benefit to organization.
• Develop “as is” – “to be” process flows.
• Coordinate Organization Change Management in alignment with the “to be” state.
• Develop and sustain productive customer relationships.
• Lead User Acceptance testing to ensure that the system addresses the business needs from the user’s point of view.
• Experience with Project Management techniques leading small to medium size projects.
• Consulting and analytical skills.
• Ability to identify finance business process improvement opportunities as it relates to industry best practices and software package out of the box functionality utilization.
• Ability to analyze risks, mitigate liabilities and negotiate solutions.

• Ability to facilitate business requirements sessions with a large number of users and produce pertinent business project documents and business process modeling documentation, including business requirements documents, with an emphasis on the Finance business areas.
• Strong communication skills – both verbal and written.
• Ability to conduct user acceptance testing, test scenario formation and communicate the results to the IT resources to drive for resolution or improvement.
• Knowledge of basic Finance and accounting principles to support key business stakeholders
• Business analysis experience within manufacturing, consumer goods, fashion and /or entertainment industries.

column1: Your Role: As a .NET Developer, you will:

column2: • Develop and maintain web applications using Active Server Pages .NET (ASP.NET), C#, and Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture.
• Work extensively with Open Data Protocol (OData) Application Programming Interfaces (APIs).
• Enhance functionality and user experience for current applications
• Write clean, scalable, and efficient code following best practices.
• Adhere to Single Responsibility, Open-Closed, Liskov Substitution, Interface Segregation, Dependency Inversion (SOLID) principles, design patterns, and object-oriented programming (OOP) concepts.
• Design, write, and optimize queries and stored procedures using Structured Query Language (SQL) Server.
• Implement end-to-end testing to ensure software quality and performance.
• Debug, test, and troubleshoot applications for smooth functionality.
• Follow version control practices using Git and GitHub.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including Quality Assurance (QA), User Interface/User Experience (UI/UX) designers, and business analysts.
• Work closely with the Product Owner to understand and deliver business requirements.

column1: Qualifications: 6 months experience in the following areas, and a strong desire to grow

column2: • Strong knowledge of C# (version 7 or later), ASP.NET (version 4 or later), MVC, APIs (OData version 3, version 4 or later), .NET Core (version 6 or later), JavaScript (ECMAScript version 5 or later), and jQuery (version 3 or later).
• Familiarity with SQL Server and database management (version 2016 or later).
• Understanding of basic data structures, algorithms, OOP principles, coding standards, and best practices.
• Experience or interest in end-to-end testing methodologies.
• Ability to write modular, reusable, and well-documented code.
• Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.
• Ability to learn new technologies and frameworks quickly.
• Excellent teamwork and communication skills.
• Stay updated with the latest .NET technologies and trends.

column2: • 10+years experience
• Uplifting/transitioning financial systems to Oracle fusion cloud.
• Ledgers, accounts payable, AR
• Expert in OTC, AR, AP, GRC how oracle interacts w/ different edge systems
• Depleted data conversion (from business perspective, not ETL)
• Data cleansing, data conversions, migrations, data cutover.
• Change management
• Data conversion from the business side – functional expert
• Previous large project experience – Client is integrating with 45 countries
• Converting open invoices to GL from business perspective,
• Experience Required:  9-14 Years
• Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, accounting or related field.
• Minimum 5+ years of experience in a finance role.
• Functional knowledge of Oracle Financials modules (version R12 or fusion), with some knowledge of Financial Analysis, Financial Consolidation, and other Financial Reporting Systems.

• Proven knowledge of Finance business processes in a large corporate finance global environment, as it relates to the Oracle Financials, and Financial Analysis and Consolidation/Planning systems, with an emphasis on Oracle Financials as well as thorough awareness of trends and developments of emerging technologies, evaluating all for appropriateness and benefit to organization.
• Develop “as is” – “to be” process flows.
• Coordinate Organization Change Management in alignment with the “to be” state.
• Develop and sustain productive customer relationships.

• Ability to facilitate business requirements sessions with a large number of users and produce pertinent business project documents and business process modeling documentation, including business requirements documents, with an emphasis on the Finance business areas.
• Strong communication skills – both verbal and written.
• Ability to conduct user acceptance testing, test scenario formation and communicate the results to the IT resources to drive for resolution or improvement.
• Knowledge of basic Finance and accounting principles to support key business stakeholders
• Business analysis experience within manufacturing, consumer goods, fashion and /or entertainment industries.

column9: Hello,Â Hope you are doing great.Â Please response me on my official email - roopesh@vizoninc.comÂ Please ensure that the resume does not exceed 5 pages.Â Job Title: AMI Business ManagerLocation: New Haven, CT- HybridÂ Advanced Metering Infrastructure (AMI) Project Manager for a long term project.Â Responsibilities may include:Develop project plans and manage budgetary needs.Host project meetings consistently with team and managers.Provide feedback, advice, project updates and encouragement to team members.Manage deadlines and push the team to ensure timeliness are metCoordinate with vendor as needed.Understand Business Needs.Work well with Business leaders to understand objectives and ensure deliverables are clearly defined and met. column9: Hi,Hope you're doing great!This is Saranya from Dizer Corp. We have an immediate requirement for aÂ RPA UiPath Lead - REMOTE.Â If you are interested, please reach out to saranyac@dizercorp.comRole: RPA (Robotic Process Automation) UiPath LeadLocation: Cary, NC (Remote)Job SummaryThe Senior Technical Lead (UiPath) oversees the UiPath projects, ensuring the successful delivery and implementation of automation solutions. They will lead a team of UiPath developers and work closely with stakeholders to gather requirements, design the automation workflows, and provide technical guidance throughout the project lifecycle.Key Responsibilities1. Lead and manage a team of UiPath developers, providing technical expertise and guidance2. Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand requirements and design automation solutions using UiPath3. Develop, test, and implement UiPath workflows to automate business processes and improve efficiency4. Troubleshoot and resolve any technical issues related to UiPath automation5. Ensure adherence to best practices and standards in UiPath development6. Provide training and mentorship to junior team members on UiPath tools and techniquesÂ Skill Requirements1. Proficient in UiPath platform, including UiPath studio, orchestrator, and robots2. Strong knowledge of RPA concepts and best practices3. Experience in developing complex automation workflows using UiPath4. Familiarity with other automation tools and technologies is a plus5. Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills6. Strong communication and leadership abilities7. Ability to work effectively in a team environment and collaborate with cross-functional teamsCertifications: UiPath Advanced Developer certification is preferredAdditional requirement:RPA UiPath Expert developer with Team leading capabilitiesÂ Thanks,Saranya ChandrasekaranTechnical Recruiter | Dizer Corp

Job Title: Sr. Snowflake Developer w/d Strong DBT Experience
Mandatory Skills: Data Engineer - DBT + Snowflake + Airflow+ SQL

column2: • Design and develop scalable data pipelines using modern data stack technologies for Cloud data platform.
• Write ETL processes, design data applications and develop data pipelines for Operational Business Intelligence Mart
• Role involves analyzing technical metadata, Data Pipeline logs and data lineage for data platform, and providing insights to support data platform operational decisions.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand and Elucidate Observability requirements for the data platform considering SLA, operational needs, DQ and proactive monitoring.
• Work with other engineers on the team to elevate technology and consistently apply best practices.
• DBT macros and overwriting
• DBT Custom Schemas
• DBT Materialization details
• Snowflake Cluster Keys
• Snowflake SQL functions
• A minimum of 12+ years of IT experience in data engineering or data management field
• 4 - 5 years of experience in application development using SQL, PLSQL
• Strong working knowledge and min of 2 years’ experience in DBT, Snowflake
• Hands-on experience with Airflow is highly preferred
• Recent experience as a Senior Data Engineer in any public cloud, preferably on Azure as well as on a cloud warehouse like Snowflake is required
• 2+ years of experience in building data pipelines using various ETL and ELT tools
• Experience in building cloud native solutions, preferably on Azure including the use of DevOps CI / CD tools and containers.
• Proven experience as a Data Analyst or in a similar role.
• Strong proficiency in Data Modelling, process metadata, observability, and monitoring data platforms.
• Familiarity with data modelling tools / techniques is a plus
• Azure or Snowflake training / certification is a plus
• Strong analytical, problem solving, communication, collaborative and organizational skills
• Self-driven, self-directed, passionate analytical and focused on delivering the right results

column9: Hello,Greetings for the day!!!Please review the below roles and advise the best time to connect with you. If you are interested, you can reach me on Linkedin:Â www.linkedin.com/in/narayanarao2 and share resumes to narayana@3mkllc.comÂ Â Hiring: Network Monitoring Engineer with particularly SolarWinds & NetCool, or Nagios & SNMP, Syslog, and NetFlow with certifications such as SolarWinds Certified Professional (SCP), Cisco (CCNA/CCNP), or equivalent are preferredLocation: RemoteRate: Open / hrContract: Long TermÂ JD:Preferred Qualifications:Experience in enterprise-scale or government IT environments.Strong knowledge of system and networking concepts.Functional knowledge of network components such as switches, routers, firewalls, proxies, and load balancers.Â Location:This position may require on-site work or be fully remote, depending on the company's policy and project requirements.Â Job Overview:We are seeking a skilled Network Monitoring Engineer to join our IT team. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with network monitoring tools, particularly SolarWinds, and will be responsible for ensuring the reliability, performance, and security of our network infrastructure through proactive monitoring and optimization.Â Key Responsibilities:Monitoring System Administration: Deploy, configure, and manage network monitoring platforms, including SolarWinds and other related tools.Proactive Monitoring: Develop and maintain dashboards, alerts, and reporting mechanisms to monitor network and system health, identifying and addressing potential issues before they impact operations.System Integration: Integrate network monitoring tools with other IT systems and platforms to streamline operations and enhance visibility.Optimization & Tuning: Analyze and optimize network monitoring configurations to ensure efficient performance and scalability.Troubleshooting: Collaborate with IT and network teams to investigate and resolve monitoring-related issues.Documentation: Create and maintain comprehensive documentation for network monitoring configurations, processes, and troubleshooting procedures.Compliance: Ensure monitoring systems adhere to security standards and regulatory compliance requirements.Team Collaboration: Work closely with cross-functional teams to define monitoring requirements and implement solutions.Â Qualifications:Experience: 3+ years of experience in network monitoring and management, with a strong focus on SolarWinds.Technical Skills: Proficiency in configuring and managing monitoring tools like SolarWinds, NetCool, or Nagios. Strong understanding of network topologies, SNMP, Syslog, and NetFlow.Scripting & Automation: Experience in scripting and automation with PowerShell, Python, or similar tools.Database Knowledge: Familiarity with databases (SQL preferred) and API integrations for monitoring tools.Certifications: Relevant certifications such as SolarWinds Certified Professional (SCP), Cisco (CCNA/CCNP), or equivalent are preferred.Soft Skills: Excellent problem-solving skills, strong communication abilities, and the capacity to work collaboratively in a team environment.Â Â Thanks & Regards,Â Narayana RaoSr Manager (Recruitments)3MK Software Solutions LLCEmail:Â narayana@3mkllc.comWebsite:Â http://3mkllc.com/Connect me on Linkedin too for daily updates and REQUIREMENTS: linkedin.com/in/narayanarao2Note:Â  WANT TO GET MY DIRECT CLIENT REQUIREMENTS DAILY? column9: Job title:Â Scrum MasterLocation: -Â Â Chicago, ILÂ Â ( Onsite ) (Only local candidates)Experience:Â  10+ YearsVisa: H1B onlyÂ Mandatory Skills:Serve, lead, coach and support one or multiple distributed cross-functional Agile Scrum Teams on the delivery of IT and business products and solutions.Accountable for their Scrum teams effectiveness.Act as Agile subject matter expert, thought leader, and mentor with extensive knowledge of Agile Scrum and SAFe processes and best practices.Responsible for planning, scheduling, and facilitating all the Scrum events.Lead risk/impediment/blocker identification, management, and resolution including coordination and facilitation across teams.Ongoing monitoring, tracking, and reporting teams delivery progress.Prepare and deliver team statuses. Manage and communicate teams releases.Support Product management to obtain healthy product backlog through coaching best practices. Manage, track, and present teams metrics include delivery and flow metrics.Â Assist in facilitating SAFe events. Lead and support their teams Planning Interval (PI) planning including preparation, facilitation, dependency management, risk identification, documentation, readout, and continuous improvement.Promote practices that ensure delivery of quality products and transparency to the maintenance of delivery progress, quality and schedule.Establish strong working relationships and promote bi-directional communication within and across teams.Maintain strong relationships within the team including product management/owner and technical subject matter experts.Develop and grow trust across the Scrum team(s), Business, and Technology.Foster an environment of continuous improvement / learning and drive improvement to the team.
